## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="7fa56-102">此枚举用于<xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.FileIO.FileSystem.DeleteDirectory%2A>和<xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.FileIO.FileSystem.DeleteFile%2A>方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7fa56-102">This enumeration is used with the <xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.FileIO.FileSystem.DeleteDirectory%2A> and <xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.FileIO.FileSystem.DeleteFile%2A> methods.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7fa56-103">为了防止意外删除了重要文件，用户**回收站**收集删除文件，并提供了还原这些文件的方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7fa56-103">To protect users against accidental deletion of important files, the **Recycle Bin** collects deleted files and provides a method for restoring those files.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7fa56-104">你必须显式删除从文件**回收站**以将其永久删除。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7fa56-104">You must explicitly delete the files from the **Recycle Bin** to make the deletion permanent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7fa56-105">直到文件将会删除从**回收站**，这些文件占用的磁盘空间不能用于其他用途。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7fa56-105">Until the files are deleted from the **Recycle Bin**, the disk space occupied by those files is unavailable for other uses.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7fa56-106">有时很有益绕过**回收站**，特别是当你要删除大量的文件 （或少量的非常大的文件），可确保是否不再需要并且想要回收磁盘空间。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7fa56-106">Sometimes it is beneficial to bypass the **Recycle Bin**, especially if you are deleting a large number of files (or a smaller number of very large files) that you are sure are no longer needed, and you want to reclaim the disk space.</span></span>  
  
 ]]></format>
